This paper deals with the problem of predicting future frames in a video, which involves learning causal rules and physical laws that govern the world. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions robotic planning, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper proposes a method that combines two distinct approaches, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
